<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Repel" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Repel,</orth> to turn away (from a love-suit): <cit><quote>foul words and frowns must not r. a lover,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 573" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 573</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I did r. his letters,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 2.1.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 1, 109</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>and he, --ed, fell into a sadness,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.146" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 146</bibl></cit> (Ff <emph>repulsed</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>